OwnerOnlyService(DiscordSocketClient, CommandHandler, DbService, IBotStrings, IBotCredentials, IDataCache, IHttpClientFactory, BotConfigService, IEnumerable<IPlaceholderProvider>, Mewdeko, GuildSettingsService, EventHandler)

Initializes a new instance of the OwnerOnlyService class. This service handles owner-only commands and functionalities for the bot.

Declaration
public OwnerOnlyService(DiscordSocketClient client, CommandHandler cmdHandler, DbService db, IBotStrings strings, IBotCredentials creds, IDataCache cache, IHttpClientFactory factory, BotConfigService bss, IEnumerable<IPlaceholderProvider> phProviders, Mewdeko bot, GuildSettingsService guildSettings, EventHandler handler)
Parameters
Type Name Description
DiscordSocketClient client

The Discord client used for interacting with the Discord API.
CommandHandler cmdHandler

Handles command processing and execution.
DbService db

Provides access to the database for data persistence.
IBotStrings strings

Provides access to localized bot strings.
IBotCredentials creds

Contains the bot's credentials and configuration.
IDataCache cache

Provides caching functionalities.
IHttpClientFactory factory

Factory for creating instances of HttpClient.
BotConfigService bss

Service for accessing bot configuration settings.
IEnumerable<IPlaceholderProvider> phProviders

A collection of providers for placeholder values.
Mewdeko bot

Reference to the main bot instance.
GuildSettingsService guildSettings

Service for accessing guild-specific settings.
EventHandler handler

Event handler for subscribing to bot events.
Remarks

The constructor subscribes to message received events and sets up periodic tasks for rotating statuses and checking for updates. It also listens for commands to leave guilds or reload images via Redis subscriptions.

LateExecute(DiscordSocketClient, IGuild, IUserMessage)

Forwards direct messages (DMs) received by the bot to the owners' DMs. This allows bot owners to monitor and respond to user messages directly.

Declaration
public Task LateExecute(DiscordSocketClient discordSocketClient, IGuild guild, IUserMessage msg)
Parameters
Type Name Description
DiscordSocketClient discordSocketClient

The Discord client through which the message was received.
IGuild guild

The guild associated with the message, if any.
IUserMessage msg

The message that was received and is to be forwarded.
Returns
Type Description
Task
Remarks

The method checks if the message was sent in a DM channel and forwards it to all owners if the setting is enabled. Attachments are also forwarded. Errors in sending messages to any owner are logged but not thrown.
